        <h1>LeetCode 396: Rotate Function (C++)</h1>
        <div class="problem-description">
            <p><strong>Problem:</strong>
                You are given an array nums. Define F(k) as the sum of i * nums[(i + k) % n] for all 0 &lt;= i &lt; n.
                Find the maximum value of F(k) for 0 &lt;= k &lt; n.
            </p>
            <p><strong>Example:</strong>
                Input: nums = [4,3,2,6]<br>
                Output: 26<br>
                Explanation: F(0) = 0*4 + 1*3 + 2*2 + 3*6 = 0 + 3 + 4 + 18 = 25. F(1) = 0*6 + 1*4 + 2*3 + 3*2 = 0 + 4 +
                6 + 6 = 16. F(2) = 0*2 + 1*6 + 2*4 + 3*3 = 0 + 6 + 8 + 9 = 23. F(3) = 0*3 + 1*2 + 2*6 + 3*4 = 0 + 2 + 12
                + 12 = 26. Maximum is 26.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="code-container">
            <button class="copy-button" onclick="copyCode(this)">Copy Code</button>
            <pre><code class="language-cpp">class Solution {
public:
    int maxRotateFunction(vector&lt;int&gt;&amp; a) {
        int n = a.size();
        if (n == 1) return 0;
        int sum = 0, f0 = 0;
        for (int i = 0; i &lt; n; i++) {
            sum += a[i];
            f0 += i * a[i];   // initial value
        }
        int best = f0, curr = f0;
        for (int i = n - 1; i &gt; 0; i--) {
            curr = curr + sum - n * a[i]; // recurrence relation
            best = max(best, curr);
        }
        return best;
    }
};</code></pre>
